    • Method Detail

      • registerCollaborator

        public java.lang.String registerCollaborator(int intType,
                                             java.lang.String fullName,
                                             java.lang.String id,
                                             java.lang.String email,
                                             java.lang.String extension)

        registerCollaborator

        Description: Registers a collaborator based on the provided information and type. This method checks for duplicate collaborators with the same ID using the searchCollaborator(String) method. If there is a duplicate collaborator, it returns a message indicating that the collaborator has already been registered. If there is no duplicate, it creates a new instance of either ImprovementCollaborator or general Collaborator based on the provided type. The newly created collaborator is then added to the list of collaborators.

        Preconditions:

        • collaborators list must be initialized.
        • searchCollaborator method should be in place.

        Postconditions:

        • A collaborator is registered based on the provided information and type, and a message indicating the success or failure of the registration is returned.
        Parameters:
        intType - The type of collaborator (1 for DTI, 2 for general).
        fullName - The full name of the collaborator.
        id - The ID of the collaborator.
        email - The email address of the collaborator.
        extension - The extension number of the collaborator.
        Returns:
        A message indicating the success or failure of the registration.

      • registerDepartment

        public java.lang.String registerDepartment(java.lang.String internalCode,
                                           java.lang.String name,
                                           java.lang.String address,
                                           int intResponsibleCollaborator)

        registerDepartment

        Description: Registers a new department in the university system with the provided internal code, name, address, and responsible collaborator.

        Preconditions:

        • internalCode, name, and address must be valid strings.
        • departments list must be initialized.
        • intResponsibleCollaborator must be a valid index representing the responsible collaborator in the list of available collaborators.

        Postconditions:

        • A new department is registered in the university system with the provided internal code, name, address, and responsible collaborator.
        • If there is available space in the departments list, the new department is added to the list.
        Parameters:
        internalCode - The internal code of the department.
        name - The name of the department.
        address - The address of the department.
        intResponsibleCollaborator - The index of the responsible collaborator in the list of available collaborators.
        Returns:
        A message indicating the success of the department registration.

      • registerRequest

        public java.lang.String registerRequest(java.lang.String subject,
                                        java.lang.String description,
                                        int intResponsibleDepartment,
                                        int intResponsibleCollaborator)

        registerRequest

        Description: Registers a new request with the specified subject, description, responsible department, and responsible collaborator. This method delegates the registration process to the Department.registerRequest(String, String, Collaborator) method of the responsible department. This method will convert the intResponsibleCollaborator to a Collaborator and the intResponsibleDepartment to a Department.

        Preconditions:

        • subject must be a valid string representing the subject of the request.
        • description must be a valid string representing the description of the request.
        • intResponsibleDepartment must be a valid index representing the responsible department.
        • intResponsibleCollaborator must be a valid index representing the responsible collaborator.

        Postconditions:

        • A new request is registered with the specified subject, description, responsible department, and responsible collaborator, and a message indicating the success of the registration is returned.
        Parameters:
        subject - The subject of the request.
        description - The description of the request.
        intResponsibleDepartment - The index of the responsible department.
        intResponsibleCollaborator - The index of the responsible collaborator.
        Returns:
        A message indicating the success of the request registration.

      • changeRequestStatus

        public java.lang.String[] changeRequestStatus(int intDepartment,
                                              int intSubject,
                                              int intStatusType)

        changeRequestStatus

        Description: Changes the status of a pending request within a department based on user input. This method retrieves the pending request from the department specified by intDepartment and invokes the Department.changeRequestStatus(int, int) method on it. The method uses getDepartmentsPendingRequest() in order to get the array of departments that have a pending requiest and then extract the actual one using the intDepartment. Finally it invokes the Department.changeRequestStatus(int, int) to enter the department and change the request.

        Preconditions:

        • intDepartment, intSubject, and intStatusType must be valid integers.
        • getDepartmentsPendingRequest() method must return a list of departments with pending requests.
        • The department index (intDepartment) must be within the range of available departments.
        • The subject index (intSubject) must be within the range of pending requests in the specified department.
        • The status type index (intStatusType) must be within the range of available status types.

        Postconditions:

        • The status of the selected pending request within the department is changed based on the provided status type.
        • The method returns a message indicating the internal code of the department, the subject of the request and the result of the status change.
        Parameters:
        intDepartment - The index of the department containing the pending request.
        intSubject - The index of the pending request within the specified department.
        intStatusType - The index representing the new status type for the request.
        Returns:
        A string array containing the internal code of the department, the subject of the request, and the message indicating the result of the status change.

      • createProject

        public java.lang.String createProject(java.lang.String name,
                                      int intPriority,
                                      int intLeader,
                                      java.lang.String responsibleDepartment,
                                      java.lang.String requestSubject,
                                      int intImpactedCommunity,
                                      int intKnowledgeType)

        createProject

        Description: Creates a new Knowledge project based on the approved request and user input. This method retrieves the accepted request using both the responsible department's internal code and the subject of the accepted request. It first searches for the department using its internal code (searchDepartment(String)) and then searches for the request within that department using its subject (Department.searchRequest(String)). After obtaining the accepted request, it identifies the leader of the project from the list of improvement collaborators(getImproveCollaborators()) Once the leader is identified, it invokes the ImprovementCollaborator.createProject(String, int, Request, int, int) method on the leader object to create the Knowledge project.

        Preconditions:

        • collaborators list must be initialized and contain collaborators.
        • intPriority, intLeader, intImpactedCommunity, and intKnowledgeType must be ints from the displayed menus.
        • The department's internal code (responsibleDepartment) must be a valid String identifier for the department.
        • The request subject (requestSubject) must be a valid String subject for an accepted request.
        • intLeader must represent a valid index corresponding to an ImprovementCollaborator.

        Postconditions:

        • A Knowledge project is created based on the provided details.
        • The project is assigned a name, priority, and other attributes based on user input.
        • The project leader is assigned based on the selected leader index.
        • The method returns a message indicating the result of the project creation.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the project.
        intPriority - The priority level of the project.
        intLeader - The index of the leader within the list of collaborators.
        responsibleDepartment - The internal code of the responsible department for the project.
        requestSubject - The subject of the accepted request.
        intImpactedCommunity - The index representing the impacted community for the project (applicable for knowledge type projects).
        intKnowledgeType - The index representing the type of knowledge project.
        Returns:
        A message indicating the result of the project creation.

      • createProject

        public java.lang.String createProject(java.lang.String name,
                                      int intPriority,
                                      int intLeader,
                                      java.lang.String responsibleDepartment,
                                      java.lang.String requestSubject,
                                      java.lang.String processCode)

        createProject

        Description: Creates a new Improvement project based on the approved request and user input. This method retrieves the accepted request by searching for the responsible department using its internal code (searchDepartment(String)) and then searching for the request within that department using its subject (Department.searchRequest(String)). It then retrieves the leader of the project from the list of improvement collaborators using getImproveCollaborators(). Once the leader is identified, it invokes the ImprovementCollaborator.createProject(String, int, Request, String) method on the leader object to create the Improvement project.

        Preconditions:

        • collaborators list must be initialized and contain collaborators.
        • intPriority, intLeader, and intResponsibleDepartment must be valid integers.
        • processCode must be a String.
        • The department's internal code (responsibleDepartment) must be a valid String identifier for the department.
        • The request subject (requestSubject) must be a valid String subject for an accepted request.
        • intLeader must represent a valid index corresponding to an ImprovementCollaborator.

        Postconditions:

        • An Improvement project is created based on the provided details.
        • The project is assigned a name, priority, and other attributes based on user input.
        • The project leader is assigned based on the selected leader index.
        • The method returns a message indicating the result of the project creation.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the project.
        intPriority - The priority level of the project.
        intLeader - The index of the leader within the list of improvement collaborators.
        responsibleDepartment - The internal code of the responsible department for the project.
        requestSubject - The subject of the accepted request.
        processCode - The process code of the project.
        Returns:
        A message indicating the result of the project creation.

      • closeProject

        public java.lang.String closeProject(int intProject,
                                     java.util.Calendar closeDate)

        closeProject

        Description: Closes a project by setting its end date. This method ensures that the entered close date is later than the registration date of the project(isEnteredDateLaterThanClassification(int, Calendar)). If the close date is valid, it sets the end date of the project to the provided close date.

        Preconditions:

        • intProject must be a valid index representing the project to be closed.
        • closeDate must be a valid Calendar object representing the close date.
        • The close date must be later than the registration date of the project.

        Postconditions:

        • The end date of the selected project is set to the provided close date.
        • A message indicating the result of the operation is returned.
        Parameters:
        intProject - The index of the project to be closed.
        closeDate - The close date to be set for the project.
        Returns:
        A message indicating the result of the project closure.

        Description: Searches for a collaborator with the specified ID. This method iterates through the array of collaborators stored in the university and checks if there is a collaborator with the provided ID. If a collaborator with the matching ID is found, it returns the collaborator object; otherwise, it returns null.

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        The collaborator object with the specified ID, if found; otherwise, null.

      • displayPendingRequests

        public java.lang.String displayPendingRequests(int intDepartment)

        displayPendingRequests

        Description: Generates a message displaying the available pending requests within the specified department. This method invokes the getDepartmentsPendingRequest() method to retrieve the list of departments with pending requests. It then retrieves the pending requests from the specified department using the provided index (Department.getPendingRequests()). Finally, it iterates through the list of pending requests to generate a formatted message containing each request's subject.

        Preconditions:

        • The getDepartmentsPendingRequest() method must return a list of departments with pending requests.
        • The department index (intDepartment) must be within the range of available departments with pending requests.
        • The getPendingRequests() method must be implemented in the Department class to retrieve pending requests.
        • The getSubject() method must be implemented in the Request class to retrieve request details.

        Postconditions:

        • A formatted message displaying the available pending requests within the specified department is generated.
        • The message contains the subject of each pending request.
        Parameters:
        intDepartment - The index of the department to display pending requests for.
        Returns:
        A message displaying the available pending requests within the specified department.

        Description: Checks if there is at least one unclosed project in the system. This method relies on the getUnclosedProjects() method to retrieve the list of unclosed projects.

      • getUnclosedProjects

        public java.util.ArrayList<Project> getUnclosedProjects()

        getUnclosedProjects

        Description: Retrieves all unclosed projects in the system. This method utilizes the getAllProjects() method to obtain a list of all projects in the system. It then iterates through each project, checking if its end date is null to determine if it is unclosed.

        Preconditions:

        • The list of all projects must be initialized and contain projects.

        Postconditions:

        • Returns an ArrayList containing all unclosed projects in the system.
        Returns:

      • showProjClassifDate

        public java.lang.String showProjClassifDate(int intProject)

        showProjClassifDate

        Description: Retrieves and formats the classification date of a specified unclosed project. This method utilizes the getUnclosedProjects() method to obtain a list of all unclosed projects, then retrieves the project at the specified index. It formats the classification date of the project and returns it as a string.

        Preconditions:

        • The list of unclosed projects must be initialized and contain projects (can't be a null)
        • intProject must be a valid index corresponding to an unclosed project.

        Postconditions:

        • Returns a formatted string indicating the classification date of the specified project.
        Parameters:
        intProject - The index of the project for which to show the classification date.
        Returns:
        A string indicating the classification date of the specified project.

      • isEnteredDateLaterThanClassification

        public boolean isEnteredDateLaterThanClassification(int intProject,
                                                    java.util.Calendar enteredDate)

        isEnteredDateLaterThanClassification

        Description: Checks if the entered date is later than the classification date of a specified project. This method retrieves the classification date of the specified project using the Project.getClassificationDate() method. It compares the entered date with the classification date and returns true if the entered date is later, false otherwise.

        Preconditions:

        • The list of all projects must be initialized and contain projects.
        • intProject must be a valid index corresponding to a project in the system.
        • enteredDate must be a valid Calendar object representing the entered date.

        Postconditions:

        • Returns true if the entered date is later than the classification date of the specified project; otherwise, returns false.
        Parameters:
        intProject - The index of the project to compare the entered date with.
        enteredDate - The entered date to compare with the classification date of the project.
        Returns:
        True if the entered date is later than the classification date of the project; otherwise, false.
